CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 17, 1965, pg. 24, reads: "Bullpen Chief - Al McBean, chief of the Pirates' bullpen, accepts congratulations from teammate Roy Face, shortly after receiving an award from The Sporting News as the top National League relief pitcher during the 1964 season. McBean and Face are expected to be the big men in Bucs' bullpen this season. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball players Elroy Face and no. 3 Al McBean, shaking hands and holding plaque inscribed "The Sporting News NL Relief Pitcher of 1964, Alvin McBean," at Forbes Field for 1965 season opener
